1. Quinque dies] This is a conventional phrase to express any short time. It occurs in S. i. 3. 16, “quinque diebus Nil erat in loculis.’'

2. Sextilem] In B. c. 8 this month first received the name of Augustus.

5. dum ficus prima calorque] See S. ii. 6. 18, n. The ‘designator' was the man who arranged the processioa at the funeral of any important person, and the ‘lictores ’ were his attendants who kept order. (See S. i. 6. 43.)
